EmailTemplate.name: Summer Intern Assignments
EmailTemplate.subject: Internship Assignments!
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hello Live Different Summer Interns!
Let me start off by saying that it has been such a pleasure getting to know you all through our phone conversations. You all are such talented young people and we are fortunate to have each and every one of you join us as a summer intern.
As you already know, there will be three assignments that we ask you to complete as part of your internship. The purpose of these assignments is to help you prepare for your time in Mexico or the DR. We want you to be as educated as possible about the country you are going to and some of the issues that it may face. We want you to feel comfortable taking on a leadership role with a large group and we want you to feel as prepared as possible.
I've attached all three assignments to this email. Please take some time to read through each assignment and know that you are always able to ask questions!
What are the assignments and when are they due?
Assignment #1: Understanding Your Country (Due April 15th) Assignment #2: The Ice Breaker Challenge (Due May 15th) Assignment #3: Human Rights Issues - What WE Can Do (Due June 15th)
What if I can't get it done by the deadline? Do I need to do them all?
All assignments are MANDATORY and MUST be completed by the deadline. If you feel that you won't be able to get an assignment done by the deadline, you must contact me at least one week prior to the due date to explain why and ask for an extension.
Will you be marking these assignments?
I won't be marking these assignments like your teachers would in school. It's based on completion. These aren't formal, essay style assignments. Completing these assignments should be a fun experience. Don't worry about making them lengthy. Try to be as concise as possible! When you get to the DR/Mexico, there will be an opportunity for you and the rest of the interns to discuss the assignments. We may even ask you to share what you have done with the rest of the interns in a presentation style! (Don't worry - I'll let you know ahead of time if we ask you to share!)
After reading through this email and the attached PDF's, please contact me if you have any questions or if there is something that is unclear. We want this to be an AWESOME experience for you and we are here to help you through every step of the way.
Thank you, Jenn
Jenn Digiandomenico Program Administrator
